      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions] Line 27: The constructor normalizes min/max and validates factors after initializing `targetBitrate_` and `lastStableBitrate_`, but it never clamps the initial bitrate to the normalized limits. A config with an initial bitrate outside the range can keep the controller target out of bounds until the next adjustment path happens to clamp it. Clamp both initialized bitrate fields after config normalization.\n```suggestion\n    targetBitrate_ \u003d clampBitrate(targetBitrate_);\n    lastStableBitrate_ \u003d targetBitrate_;\n```\n",
      "revId": "0a53ec08db576918e178cd7a89e1128b402ffc5d",
