      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions] Line 657: The Android jitter guard is wrapped in `#if !__ANDROID__`, but `__ANDROID__` may be undefined on non-Android builds. Some compilers treat undefined identifiers in preprocessor expressions as `0`, but this is fragile and can trigger `-Wundef`/warning-as-error builds. Use the existing portable pattern.\n```suggestion\n#ifndef __ANDROID__\n            if (rtcpi.jitter \u003c\u003d 1000)\n#endif\n```\n",
